:{{A|VO side1 tp bronya 111.ogg}} '''Bronya:''' Yes... I'm afraid so.
:{{A|VO side1 tp mar7th 184.ogg}} '''March 7th:''' That's ridiculous! And what's with the timing? What took them so long to get here? If it wasn't for us eliminating the Stellaron, they'd have nothing to collect! It's obvious they're just trying to take advantage.
:{{A|VO side1 tp bronya 112.ogg}} '''Bronya:''' According to her account, the repayment period agreed upon by the Architects and the IPC investors was... 280 years. However, less than a century after the loan was taken out, the connection between Jarilo-VI and the rest of the galaxy was completely severed.
:{{A|VO side1 tp bronya 113.ogg}} '''Bronya:''' The IPC deemed that the disaster had caused irreparable damage and that there was no civilization left to reclaim the debt from. As such, they considered the owed sum permanently lost...
:{{A|VO side1 tp bronya 114.ogg}} '''Bronya:''' ...It wasn't until the Stellaron crisis was resolved that the IPC discovered that Belobog had survived...
:{{A|VO side1 tp mar7th 185.ogg}} '''March 7th:''' And that's when they sent Topaz over to collect the debt...
:{{A|VO side1 tp bronya 115.ogg}} '''Bronya:''' ...And the interest.
:{{DIcon|Arrow}} How much is owed?
::{{A|VO side1 tp bronya 116.ogg}} '''Bronya:''' An astronomical amount. I don't even know how to read such a long string of numbers.
:{{DIcon|Arrow}} What happens if you don't pay it off in time?
::{{A|VO side1 tp bronya 117.ogg}} '''Bronya:''' The debt owed is an astronomical amount. I don't even know how to read such a long string of numbers.
:{{A|VO side1 tp bronya 118.ogg}} '''Bronya:''' Before you both arrived, Topaz warned me that if payments were delayed, the IPC would give her the authority to employ "strong measures."
:{{A|VO side1 tp mar7th 186.ogg}} '''March 7th:''' I had no idea things were like this. Here I was thinking the IPC had come to rebuild Belobog, not extort it!
:{{DIcon|Arrow}} Looks like we'll have to intervene.
::{{A|VO side1 tp mar7th 187.ogg}} '''March 7th:''' Yeah! We have to help Bronya out! The IPC is too big and powerful &mdash; the Belobogians won't be able to resolve this problem on their own.
:{{DIcon|Arrow}} I doubt the Belobogians can do anything about this on their own...
::{{A|VO side1 tp mar7th 188.ogg}} '''March 7th:''' Right, we need to figure out how to help them. The IPC is too big and powerful &mdash; even if Bronya steps in, it'll be hard for her to resolve the situation...
:{{A|VO side1 tp bronya 119.ogg}} '''Bronya:''' You seem to have a deeper knowledge of the Interastral Peace Corporation than I do, but if the records are accurate and they truly have a presence throughout the galaxy, the IPC could crush Belobog like a bug if they wanted to.
